&gt; &gt; Full credit to Steve Hultay for discovering the hackability of this
&gt; &gt; radio, and as he had mentioned in the past, it really wasn&#39;t the
&gt; &gt; easiest. After tearing it apart, cutting, desoldering, etc...to 
&gt; locate
&gt; &gt; the mute wire/pin/solder pad, I found out that it can be one of the
&gt; &gt; easiest hacks out there. 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; Rather than disassembling and such, simply cut the trace on each 
&gt; side
&gt; &gt; of the mute pin solder pad. Takes about 30 seconds with a hobby 
&gt; knife.
&gt; &gt; I felt really stupid after 4 hours taking everything apart and
&gt; &gt; desoldering wires, etc...
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; instructions with photos can be found on my blog if interested. 
